      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T09:07:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`super.handlerAdded(ctx)` publishes `channel` via a volatile write, and `invoke()` can then run on an application thread after seeing `channel !\u003d null`. But `bootstrap` is assigned only after that volatile write, so the same thread is not guaranteed to see it initialized and can hit NPE at `bootstrap.open()`.\nIMO, we can assign bootstrap before super.handlerAdded(ctx)",
      "revId": "0ea583145ea606064fadc200833b7c3a35a2fefa",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
